From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Fri, 23 May 2026 22:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ask: route HIT-path CC actions through no-confirm TX FQ

PR14z23 consumer of the dpaa_alloc_offload_tx_fq() export added in
patch 0053.

ask_hw_resolve_oif_tx_fqid() previously called dpaa_get_tx_fqid(),
which returned the kernel-managed egress FQ priv->egress_fqs[0] — the
same queue dpaa_xmit() uses for the slow path.  Every silicon-HIT
frame whose CC action targets this FQID therefore inherits the
per-frame TX-confirmation FD enqueue that dpaa_eth_napi_poll()
processes via the per-CPU TX-confirm FQ.  At ~1.6 Mpps egress this is
the ~16% NET_KERNEL_CPU floor that pins the M2 acceptance gate above
the 5% target (see PR14z22 step-1 measurement and PR14z23-DESIGN.md
"Architectural conclusion").

Replace the resolver with one that allocates (once, per peer OIF) a
dedicated no-confirm TX FQ via dpaa_alloc_offload_tx_fq(), caches the
returned FQID in a small static table, and hands it back to the
flow-insert path.  The CC node's per-key FORWARD_FQ action now lands
each HIT frame on a queue whose context_a has B0V=0 — FMan still
transmits the frame on the wire but silicon does NOT enqueue a
TX-confirmation FD.  dpaa_eth_napi_poll() therefore has nothing to
process for offloaded traffic.

Kernel-driven TX (dpaa_xmit, ARP, miss-action fallthrough,
control-plane) is unaffected: it continues to use priv->egress_fqs[]
which retains the existing confirmation path.  Only frames whose
match resolves to an FMan PCD CC HIT bypass the confirmation step.

The cache is a small fixed-size array keyed by netdev ifindex modulo
ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ; collisions fall back to the slow path
(re-allocation) but this is negligible because there are at most 5
DPAA netdevs on the board.  The cache is read under RTNL so an
ifindex collision will not corrupt state — at worst a duplicate
FQ is allocated, which is leaked at port-remove time via the standard
priv->dpaa_fq_list cleanup the helper already participates in.

Failure modes:

  - dpaa_alloc_offload_tx_fq() returns -ENODEV / -ENOMEM / -ENOENT:
    propagate to the flow-insert caller which falls back to the SW
    path (the same behaviour as the old dpaa_get_tx_fqid() error
    propagation).

  - Cache slot already populated with a different OIF (hash
    collision): allocate a fresh no-confirm FQ for this OIF; do
    NOT reuse the cached entry (it belongs to a different netdev).
    This keeps correctness over performance for an edge case that
    cannot occur on Mono Gateway DK.

Signed-off-by: ASK2 build bot <ask2-build@kralj.dev>
---
 .../net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c  | 79 +++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 73 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
@@ -5095,21 +5095,88 @@ static bool mac_is_zero(const u8 m[ETH_ALEN])
 }
 
 /*
- * ask_hw_resolve_oif_tx_fqid() — look up the peer netdev's per-queue
- * TX FQID via the in-tree export from patch 0031.  Returns the FQID
- * the OH-port AD chain's trailing FORWARD_FQ should aim at.  -ENODEV
- * propagates from non-DPAA netdevs so the caller knows to SW-fallback.
+ * PR14z23: per-OIF no-confirm TX FQ cache.
+ *
+ * Each entry is a single OIF -> FQID mapping.  ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ
+ * is sized to fit all five DPAA netdevs (eth0..eth4) on the Mono Gateway
+ * DK with margin; on collision (a previously cached OIF re-hashes here
+ * with a different ifindex) we fall back to allocating a fresh FQ for
+ * this OIF without overwriting the prior entry, keeping correctness
+ * over performance.
+ */
+#define ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ 16
+
+struct ask_hw_offload_tx_cache_entry {
+u32 oif;/* ifindex; 0 = empty */
+u32 fqid;
+};
+
+static struct ask_hw_offload_tx_cache_entry
+ask_hw_offload_tx_cache[ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ];
+
+/*
+ * ask_hw_resolve_oif_tx_fqid() — resolve the OIF to a no-confirm
+ * TX FQID for the silicon HIT path.  Allocates (and caches) a
+ * dedicated FQ_TYPE_TX_NO_CONFIRM FQ on first use via the in-tree
+ * export dpaa_alloc_offload_tx_fq() from patch 0053.
+ *
+ * The CC node's per-key FORWARD_FQ action will point at the
+ * returned FQID; matched frames are TX'd on the wire by FMan
+ * without a per-frame TX-confirm FD enqueue, eliminating the
+ * dpaa_eth_napi_poll() per-frame work on the HIT path.
+ *
+ * Returns -ENODEV / -ENOMEM / -ENOENT from the underlying
+ * allocator; the caller treats any error as SW-fallback (the same
+ * contract as the old dpaa_get_tx_fqid()-based resolver).
  */
 static int ask_hw_resolve_oif_tx_fqid(u32 oif, u32 *fqid)
 {
+struct ask_hw_offload_tx_cache_entry *slot;
 struct net_device *dev;
+u32 cached;
 int rc;
 
+/* RTNL is held by the flow-offload caller chain; the cache is
+ * only mutated from this code path so a plain read/write is
+ * sufficient. */
+ASSERT_RTNL();
+
+slot = &ask_hw_offload_tx_cache[oif % ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ];
+if (slot->oif == oif) {
+cached = READ_ONCE(slot->fqid);
+if (cached) {
+*fqid = cached;
+return 0;
+}
+}
+
 rcu_read_lock();
 dev = dev_get_by_index_rcu(&init_net, oif);
 if (!dev) {
 rcu_read_unlock();
 return -ENODEV;
 }
-rc = dpaa_get_tx_fqid(dev, /*queue=*/0, fqid);
+rc = dpaa_alloc_offload_tx_fq(dev, fqid);
 rcu_read_unlock();
+if (rc)
+return rc;
+
+/* Populate the cache slot only if it was empty or matched this
+ * OIF.  A genuine hash collision (different OIF already cached
+ * at this slot) leaves the slot untouched — the freshly allocated
+ * FQ for this OIF is still returned but a subsequent call for the
+ * same OIF will re-allocate.  On Mono Gateway DK with 5 DPAA
+ * netdevs and SZ=16, collisions are statistically impossible. */
+if (slot->oif == 0 || slot->oif == oif) {
+slot->oif = oif;
+WRITE_ONCE(slot->fqid, *fqid);
+pr_info("ask: hw: cached no-confirm TX FQID 0x%x for oif=%u\n",
+*fqid, oif);
+} else {
+pr_warn("ask: hw: offload TX cache collision at slot %u "
+"(cached oif=%u, new oif=%u) — allocating without "
+"caching\n",
+oif % ASK_HW_OFFLOAD_TX_CACHE_SZ, slot->oif, oif);
+}
 return rc;
 }
 
